26/02/26

1) to change the timestamp for the newly created file with the already existing file

    [touch -r oldfile newfile]

2) to check the timestamp

    [stat filename]

3) to create nested directory at once

    [mkdir -p snowflake/day1/logs]    

    snowflake 
    day1(inside snowflake)
    logs(inside day1)

4) Find files modified in last 30 minutes

    [find /data -mmin -30]

5) Find empty files

    [find . -type f -size 0]
     Very common in pipeline debugging    

6) Check which folder is consuming space

    [du -sh *]

7) Find duplicate IDs

   [sort data.csv | uniq -d]    

8) Extract 3rd column from CSV

   [awk -F',' '{print $3}' data.csv]

9) if script not executing

    [chmod +x run.sh]   

10) to check the latest logs 
    [tail -f a.log]   tail -f = live monitoring

11) to identify large files consuming disk space
    [du -ah /data | sort -rh | head -5]   

12) search error in all log files
    [grep -i "error" *.log] 
    [grep -i "error" /data/logs]   #recursive search

13) to check if the job is running multiple times
    [ps -ef | grep job_name | grep -v grep | wc -l]    


